 Amendment is constitutionally infirm because it conflicts with law school recruiting policies, which are \u8220\'3fsaturated with First Amendment value\u8221\'3f and lie at the intersection of three distinct First Amendment rights (academic freedom, freedom of expressive association, and free speech). Plaintiffs\rquote  position is that application of three distinct constitutional doctrines (the doctrine of unconstitutional conditions, the prohibition against viewpoint discrimination, and the void-for-vagueness doctrine) compels a finding of unconstitutionality. The Government disagrees and relies heavily on Congress\rquote  broad power under the Spending Clause and its constitutional mandate to raise and support armies.
