 The Court believes that this difference is constitutionally significant. As the presence of military recruiters on campuses or job fairs does not significantly affect the law schools\rquote  ability to espouse or advocate their own viewpoints, Plaintiffs\rquote  claim of expressive association fails the second prong of the framework established in 
}
