 Additionally, as already stated, law schools are free to take ameliorative actions to disclaim any endorsement of the military\rquote s recruiting policy; in fact, law schools can outright denounce the military without running afoul of the Solomon Amendment\rquote s prohibitions. For the non-communicative impact of their conduct, and for nothing else, will law schools transgress the Solomon Amendment. 
