 (holding \u8220\'3fundeniably opaque\u8221\'3f terms capable of raising significant vagueness concerns in certain contexts not unconstitutionally vague in selective subsidies context). Economic regulation, for example, is subject to a \u8220\'3fless strict vagueness test\u8221\'3f because it often deals with narrowly defined circumstances and because \u8220\'3fbusinesses, which face economic demands to plan behavior carefully, can be expected to consult relevant legislation in advance of action.\u8221\'3f 
