{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The military \u8220\'3fgaining entry\u8221\'3f to campuses plainly contemplates entering the campus gates. To enter something is \u8220\'3fto go or come into\u8221\'3f it. 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Webster\rquote s Third New International Dictionary
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 756 (2003). Access is defined as \u8220\'3fpermission, liberty, or ability to enter, approach, communicate with.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 at 11. Thus, to comply with the Solomon Amendment, a school must allow the military to come onto campus and to communicate with interested students for purposes of recruiting. Schools that do not allow the military on campus, and thereby prohibit on-campus recruitment, do not comply with the statutory requirements. The statute is abundantly clear in that respect.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Schools that allow the military on campus, yet \u8220\'3fin effect prevent\u8221\'3f military recruiting efforts also do not comply with the Solomon Amendment. The phrase in effect means \u8220\'3fvirtually\u8221\'3f or \u8220\'3fin substance,\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 at 724, and the term prevents means \u8220\'3fto keep from happening,\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 at 1798. \u8220\'3fIn effect prevents\u8221\'3f therefore contemplates virtually keeping the military from recruiting students or posing obstacles that would normally lead to abandonment of the recruiting effort.
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Importantly, Congress chose not to use language connoting anything less than a total or effective prohibition on the military\rquote s recruitment efforts, such as \u8220\'3finterfere,\u8221\'3f \u8220\'3fhinder,\u8221\'3f \u8220\'3fimpede,\u8221\'3f or \u8220\'3fadversely affect.\u8221\'3f It follows that anything short of preventing or totally thwarting the military\rquote s recruitment efforts does not trigger funding denial pursuant to the statute. Although it is conceivable that assistance provided to other employers (which thereby facilitates those employers\rquote  recruiting efforts) could, under certain circumstances, rise to the level of \u8220\'3fin effect prevent[ing]\u8221\'3f military recruitment efforts, the fact \u8220\'3f[t]hat there may be marginal cases in which it is difficult to determine the side of the line on which a particular fact situation falls is no sufficient reason to hold the language too ambiguous\u8221\'3f to pass constitutional muster. 
}
