We agree with the District Court that soliciting and proselytizing are obvious forms of expressive activity. We part, however, on the notion that efforts to raise a legal staff are \u8220\'3feconomic or functional\u8221\'3f while efforts to raise funds and membership are not. Recruiting, soliciting and proselytizing are similarly economic and functional and, at the same time, similarly expressive. Recruiting conveys the message that \u8220\'3four organization is worth working for,\u8221\'3f while soliciting and proselytizing convey the similar functional message that \u8220\'3four charity is worth giving to\u8221\'3f or \u8220\'3four cause is worth joining.\u8221\'3f
