Background:
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Association of law schools and law faculties brought suit challenging constitutionality of Solomon Amendment, which required Department of Defense (DOD) to deny federal funding to institutions of higher education that prohibited military representatives access to and assistance for recruiting purposes. The United States District Court for the District of New Jersey, John C. Lifland, J., 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2003850071&pubNum=4637&originatingDoc=I2ac5d716ad1811daa20eccddde63d628&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.DocLink)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
291 F.Supp.2d 269,
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 denied association\rquote s motion for preliminary injunction. Association appealed. The United States Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2005599806&pubNum=506&originatingDoc=I2ac5d716ad1811daa20eccddde63d628&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.DocLink)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
390 F.3d 219,
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 reversed and remanded, concluding that amended version of Solomon Amendment, codifying DOD policy, violated the unconstitutional conditions doctrine because it forced law school to choose between surrendering its First Amendment rights and losing federal funding for its university. Certiorari was granted.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Holdings:
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The Supreme Court, Chief Justice 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0258116001&originatingDoc=I2ac5d716ad1811daa20eccddde63d628&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.DocLink)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Roberts
}}}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb400 
, held that
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Solomon Amendment requires that, in order for law school and its university to receive federal funding, the law school must offer military recruiters the same access to its campus and students that it provides to the nonmilitary recruiter receiving the most favorable access;
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
