Section 6\u8211\'3f4 of the By\u8211\'3fLaws of the AALS requires member schools to, among other things, provide \u8220\'3fstudents and graduates with equal opportunity to obtain employment, without discrimination or segregation\u8221\'3f on the basis of sexual orientation and other protected categories. (Rosenkranz Decl. \u182\'3f 10, Ex. 1). Schools must communicate to employers their \u8220\'3ffirm expectation\u8221\'3f 
