 The record reveals that the law schools, too, seek to inculcate a certain set of values and principles in their students. Plaintiffs assert that the law schools believe that invidious discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation is a moral wrong, and that \u8220\'3fjudgments about people bearing no relation to merit harm and inhibits students, faculty, and eventually society at large.\u8221\'3f Plaintiffs further assert that their non-discrimination policies help inculcate those values. And whereas the Boy Scouts Oath and Law did not expressly mention the particular value that it claimed the government was undermining\u8212\'3fhomosexual conduct as an unacceptable form of behavior\u8212\'3fthe law schools\rquote  non-discrimination policies explicitly include sexual orientation.
