 (\u8220\'3f[T]he court, as well as the agency, must give effect to the unambiguously expressed intent of Congress.\u8221\'3f) (\u8220\'3fThe judiciary is the final authority on issues of statutory construction and must reject administrative constructions which are contrary to clear congressional intent.\u8221\'3f). By letter dated May 29, 2003, Acting Deputy Under\u8211\'3fSecretary of Defense William Carr stated that the DOD interpreted 
