{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs18 \sa200 \sb0 
The Court does not share Plaintiffs\rquote  view that the DOD\rquote s current posture is predominantly an effort to suppress the law schools\rquote  messages of non-discrimination. Plaintiffs\rquote  arguments to the contrary are not convincing since they are unsupported by factual evidence which goes directly to any improper motivation. The evidence supplied suggests that the DOD is attempting to enforce the law as they currently construe it.
\par 
}
}
